Now I have a clear understanding. The current is_about UNION branch in the  
  SPARQL query only looks at annotation axiom xrefs on the species-neutral PR 
  class itself, which finds very few (7) UniProt IDs. The correct approach is 
  to follow is_about → species-neutral PR class → human-specific subclass (via
  rdfs:subClassOf + only_in_taxon some NCBITaxon_9606) → UniProtKB:* xref.    
  This resolves 2,869 UniProt IDs for human proteins.                         
                                                                              
  Let me update the SPARQL query:

View src/sparql/uniprot-efo-map.sparql
prefix oio: <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#>              
     prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>                             
     prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>                     
     prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>                
     prefix obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>                            
                                                                              
     SELECT DISTINCT ?term ?term_label ?uniprot_id                            
                                                                              
     WHERE {                                                                  
       {                                                                      
         # Active measurement terms with direct UniProt xrefs                 
         ?term rdf:type owl:Class ;                                           
           rdfs:subClassOf+ <http://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/EFO_0001444> ;          
           oio:hasDbXref ?uniprot_id .                                        
         OPTIONAL {                                                           
           ?term rdfs:label ?term_label .                                     
         }                                                                    
         FILTER(isIRI(?term))                                                 
         FILTER(STRSTARTS(?uniprot_id, "uniprot:"))                           
       } UNION {                                                              
         # Measurement terms with is_about -> protein -> UniProtKB xref on    
  annotation axiom                                                            
         ?term rdf:type owl:Class ;                                           
           rdfs:subClassOf+ <http://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/EFO_0001444> ;          
           rdfs:subClassOf [ owl:onProperty obo:IAO_0000136 ;                 
                             owl:someValuesFrom ?protein ] .                  
         ?axiom owl:annotatedSource ?protein ;                                
